HEADWORD: Mustelidae
<hw>Mustelidae</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A natural family of
fissiped fur-bearing carnivorous mammals including the weasels;
polecats; ferrets; minks; fishers; otters; badgers; skunks; wolverines;
and martens.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Mustelidae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

